manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Commander FP – 10 Port Hub for PWM Fans The new Thermaltake’s PWM fan hub Commander FP is capable of powering up to 10 independent PWM fans which allows users to saturate the case with fans while maintaining superb cable management. Sporting a blue LED indicator light, the Commander FP ensures the inside of your case looks just as good as the outside, making it the best choice for cooling performance enthusiasts or users seeking no-fuss installation!

10 Independent PWM Fans Supported Capable of connecting 10 PWM fans for speed-control* simultaneously, the Commander FP enables users to optimally expand cooling capability within the chassis and enjoy greater system performance. * Only the channel port (Port 1) with glossy side support RPM signal detection. The rest fans will run at the same DUTY RATIO. * 3 pin fans will run at FULL SPEED

Convenient SATA Power Input Designed with a stable SATA power input in mind, the Commander FP safely and reliably powers up to 10 PWM fans simultaneously*. Direct power from PSU prevents stray current when the fan hub is in use. * Only the channel port (Port 1) with glossy side support RPM signal detection. The rest fans will run at the same DUTY RATIO. High Quality Symmetrical Design Sporting a symmetrical design, the Commander FP uses high-quality textured plastic in its construction. Arc trim on both sides gives the Commander FP a sleek, modern look that matches its superior performance. Neat Cable Management Featuring a blue LED indicator for access indication, Commander FP provides superb cable management which allows users to experience the unrivaled airflow and water cooling capabilities.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works for fans, pumps, lights, etc
reviews.reviewText: I used several of these daisy chained together to power a cooling loop and about 20 fans. Allows you to use a single fan header for everything and relays control signal throughout the daisychain. Would definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Wasn't sure about this fan controller at first. Used it for an itx build. The motherboard only had one system fan plug and I was using six fans (I believe the cooler the better lol) all fan speeds are controlled by the first plug on the controller. Works as advertised!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars powers multiple fans
reviews.reviewText: used this due to the corsair commander not having enough power to power the fans alotted for their very own case. Tried a splitter but the corsair commander just fails to power anything more than one of their own fans. to reset the corsair commander after it fails is laughable and its just easier to buy this and be done with it. I did lose some functionality in addressing the colors, but the fans work and the case is now cool.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 8, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of the best fan controllers right now
reviews.reviewText: I have been using 2 of these for a few months now, powered by separate sata cables, powering 10 noctua fans on each fan controller at full speeds most of the time. These have been very reliable and do not get warm to the touch either. I have them stacked ontop of each other to save space. Not many name brand quality fan controllers available these days I can vouch that these are safe so far and work. You cannot control each fan individually, it follows which ever fan speed is connected to the shiny/glossy port.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does The Job
reviews.reviewText: What can I say about this product besides it does what it is supposed to and is easy to install. It looks cool enough but its going in your cable management back compartment of your PC so not that important. I have like 5 fans hooked up to this unit and it has worked great for over 3 months now. Ultimately the only thing that could bring this product rating down would be if it does not stand the test of time, and thus far it has. For those reasons I'M IN on this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I was skeptical at first when I saw someone caught this product on fire. I honestly laughed about it, as this product works great for my fans in my case. You just have to plug the header coming from the device into a fan header on your motherboard that isn't your main CPU fan header. READ YOUR MOTHERBOARD MANUAL before installing to a fan header on your motherboard. This product is great for my use and all the fans speed up and down as they should. Make sure you have PWM mode enabled for the specific fan header you plugged this device into so all fans can work properly. I would recommend this product to anyone who needs a PWM fan splitter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great with ASUS ROG Strix motherboards
reviews.reviewText: Like many people in the market for a product like this, I build a PC with a 5 fan design, but my motherboard only has three headers for case fans. This product is straight forward and works great. It extends the 4-pin fan support of my ASUS motherboard and gives me ample outputs for additional fans.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Should be installed with magnets
reviews.reviewText: I mean it works as a fan board but the installation is done with 3M like velcro that does not stick very well. This board should have magnetics to install not cheap velcro tape. The wire that connects to the fan controller on the MB is also loose fitting. If you're not careful it can just fall out because reasons

reviews.reviewTitle: Its Great for Single Zone Control!
reviews.reviewText: I desperately needed a Fan Hub after my Capacitor for the CPU fan headers popped. This stood in for a good while until I had to change they types of fans in the system. While it has many connectors for fans, it only has one to the mainboard. sadly it is only controllable up to the lowest speed fan attached to the device. (So if you have two types of fans, one 1000rpm one and two 1600rpm ones it only reads the theoretical maximum of the 1000rpm and the others aren't full speed.) maybe if not connected to the mainbaord it boosts all to max? but that would be too loud.Not complaining, only downsides, great device for what it does. Still highly recommended for similar zone control. (IE Front / Rear / Side) (Top / Top / Bottom) (Front x3 / Top x3) Its generally best to have the GPU sidefan on a separate controller to give it a more direct pressurized environment FYI.
Funciona como debe de ser. Me parece que está a excelente precio.

Eine sehr nützliche Sache wenn man 10 Lüfter im Gehäuse hat aber nur 4 Stecker am Mainboard für die Lüfter 😅. Mein Gehäuse ist ebenfalls von Thermaltake, aus diesem Grund kaufte ich es auch von der selben Firma.
Very easy to set up, affordable, and works like a charm. Thanks TK, reliable products as always
Using this in my PC as a hub, which was needed because of fan issues. It works great.
